items.name: Elizaveta
items.description:
Elizaveta (Summer Breeze)

Active: 2009-2015

Introduction

This is my first character LoRA. I hope you like her as much as I do.

Training Data

This LoRA was trained with close up images of her face and upper body. Most images were nudes so add strong clothing promps and negative promps if you don't want nudes.

Image count: 77

Resolution: 512x768

Model

Real Hot Mix v1, but also works with other models.

How to use

Generate a txt2img image, send to img2img and upscale. Don't use Restore Faces as this will change her face to some random face. Upscaling also improves the face.

Inpainting minor parts of her mouth and eyes also helps to fix some problems. Inpainting the whole face is possible but takes time.

For best results I am using ControlNet with type tile + Ultimate SD upscale to keep the image stable. Upscale 2-3x works most of the time.

items.name: Fletcher (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Fletcher from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 278 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

This LoRa Weighting: [1 - 0.7]

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

items.name: Noir Diffusion V.1 - Noir aesthetics embedding
items.description:
It has a tendency to black and white photography as it was intended. It can make colour pictures obviously, just write it down in the negative prompts if you don't want "black and white photography".

This is just a first approach to the noir aesthetics of movies from the decade of 40's and 50's. As a enjoyer of the noir genre myself, I'm not convinced (at all!) by the native "noir" aesthetics of SD 1.5 so I'm working towards something with more fidelity to the aforementioned old movies from the golden era which includes hairstyles, lightning, clothes and so on.

My intentions is expanding the dataset -hugely-, fine-tuning and test the limits of the embedding format.

All the dataset is conformed by Noir classics (1939-1949).

If you like my embeddings, please consider to support my work in https://ko-fi.com/punkimaster

items.name: Ultra Instinct Effect LoRA
items.description:
Ultra Instinct effect LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

I need to thank Kanye from the WD Discord for this.
I've always wanted to make a UI lora, but lacked data for it. Kanye made one a while ago, which was very hard to use because the dataset was only made with Goku pics from the anime (can't be helped). However he showed me how to control it in order to get something that wasn't Goku all the time.

So I got a little creative. I left my PC running to generate around 5k images of various subjects overnight, then I selected around 150 good ones (mainly females) and I integrated it with anime screencaps of Goku. After training the lora I merged it with by DBS style lora at -0.44 weight to further reduce the style overfitting.
This is now my second lora from synthetic data and I'm not really a fan of the process :D

I don't think the results are perfect (that's why I disabled the comments) and the lora is still difficult to control, but at least it's now easy to get girls and different characters.

Should work fine at around weight 1 on most models. I tested AnyLoRA, AAM, DreamShaper, NED, AbsoluteReality and even Western Ani Diffusion. Use ultrainstinct, aura to increase fidelity and look at the example prompts.

Also remember to use ADetailer for full body images, as well as highres fix.

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: MyBreastHelper
items.description:
Like my work? Consider donating.

I've used many different breast sizing LoRA's in the past and I really just wanted to give it a try. Mainly because I'm rarely happy with the range of most of them unless they are dedicated to the size I am trying to accomplish. (like flat chest) I've also been trying to refine my LoRA making skills so this was another opportunity for that.

I wish you the breast day ever!

MBH-TT & MBHU-TT2 Check "About this version" for small notes on the added triggers for each version.

This has become the combination of MyBreastHelper and ASSet Manager. There is so much going on in this LoRA now that I can't say it all in a short summary.

Things to remember.

  1. Order matters! you might have the right mix of prompts but in the wrong order to get the result you want.

  2. Negative prompt what you don't want. Single triggers work pretty well but each one has a tendency to influence other parts of the body.

  3. Use corresponding "common" body tags when needed in both positive and negative prompts. This helps when you're trying for a contradiction in say breast size vs. body type. Skinny woman with big breasts or a chubby woman with small breasts.

  4. Use weights to your advantage. Sometimes you almost get what you want but need a small tweak. don't be afraid to use a trigger with a low weight like (saggy breasts:0.2)

As always please share those beautiful creations.

modelVersions.name: MBHU-TT2F
trainedWords: all triggers from MBH-TT and the following
modelVersions.description:
I thought I was done with this. There have been 5 main improvements/additions. Everything from total torso remains the same but I was unhappy with the eyes I was getting, freckles were showing up like painted on dots, pubic hair was unreliable and fake looking most times, and faces were suffering likely due to all the cropped-out chins from the other training images. Tattoos were simply something I have considered in the past.

Best overall lora weight is 0.8 in my testing and you will still want to start with a lower trigger weight on tags like "face freckles" and "hairy pussy". Hairy pussy is capable of going from stubble to Wookie.

Body tattoos will range from sleeve tattoos only, then chest, then stomach. (usually)

I included the eye color tags simply to show which were baked in but with an added bonus, "2tn eyes" If you know someone with hazel eyes or they say their eyes change color, these are those eyes. It's tricky to get a specific combination but even used by itself can result in a much more dynamic eye color.

The fifth improvement is a more subtle one. There are no triggers for it. twenty-six images of high resolution (1080 and higher) portraits were added with full BLIP captioning. Portraits of actresses and completely random people also.

The overall dataset image count without counting regularization images is now at 1325. I don't currently have any plans to add anything else to this project, but that's what I thought last time.

(For anyone wondering, the F in the name is simply my way of tracking how many times I tried different training methods, this was my 6th attempt at this version.

Lora权重大约在0.5-0.8。示例图像不得不使用巨大的乳房，你懂的。“koga yuika”提示词似乎不是必须的，只要写其他的tags就能生成她本人，除了头发的颜色以外应该都能改变。上传的文件为epoch 14，简单做了所有epoch的对比图，也许epoch 14不是最佳的。

koga yuika, blonde hair, short hair, green eyes, green hair ribbon, light blue tied shirt, loose tied shirt, purple shirt, pleated skirt, pink skirt,

koga yuika, blonde hair, short hair, green eyes, maid, cat ears, cat tail, garter straps, blue thighhighs, black hairband, fake animal ears, animal ear fluff, choker, zettai ryouiki,

koga yuika, blonde hair, short hair, green eyes, red bowtie, green hair ribbon, white thighhighs, long collared shirt, green skirt, plaid skirt, pleated skirt, zettai ryouiki,

由于素材原因生成的都是卷起袖子的衣服，在 negative 中添加 sleeves rolled up 可能可以改善。

modelVersions.name: PinEnchantedPlus+
modelVersions.description: Hello, this model is an update of PinEnchanted that improves some aspects of the previous model. Some styles and LoRas have been added to the previous style, significantly improving aspects like the eyes, composition, dynamism, etc., while trying to respect the base style of PinEnchanted. I hope you enjoy it. Some tips for using this version: Use "Adetailer." It really helps with the images. Use the "4xAnimeSharp" scaler, and I also recommend using ControlNet with color models. They generate unexpected but very appealing results!!

works with most styles - weight could be 0.6 - 0.9 - trained for 768 (can have better results)

to get close to her old design try any of these - or put in Neg to reduce chance( when altering appearance/outfit)

For appearance

Betty. long purple hair, (green and red heterochromia) ,makeup, plump

for attire

BetClo, green jewerly, fingerless gloves, argyle legwear, high heels, orange shorts ,crown hat, belt, orange bra,

  • right eye is green, Left is red, ( respected eyeshadows are swapped) but the small details for make-up are minor

  • removal of plump may slim her down, full body shots don't work to well,

  • hands and fingers may be more of an issue than usual

  • exploding backgrounds are related
